<h2>pecto init</h2>
<p>Analyze a project and generate behavior specs.</p>
<pre><code>pecto init [path] [--format yaml|json] [--output file] [--verbose] [--quiet]</code></pre>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>path</code></td><td><code>.</code></td><td>Project directory to analyze</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--format, -f</code></td><td><code>yaml</code></td><td>Output format</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--output, -o</code></td><td>stdout</td><td>Write to file instead of stdout</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--verbose, -v</code></td><td>off</td><td>Per-capability breakdown</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>--quiet, -q</code></td><td>off</td><td>Suppress status, only print spec</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Examples</h3>
<pre><code># Analyze current directory
pecto init

# Save as JSON
pecto init ./my-app --format json --output specs.json

# Verbose output for debugging
pecto init ./my-app --verbose

# Pipe-friendly (no stderr)
pecto init ./my-app --quiet > specs.yaml</code></pre>

<hr />

<h2>pecto show</h2>
<p>Show the spec for a specific capability.</p>
<pre><code>pecto show &lt;name&gt; [--path .]</code></pre>

<p>Supports substring matching. If not found, lists available capabilities.</p>

<pre><code>pecto show user-service
pecto show user  # matches any capability containing "user"</code></pre>

<hr />

<h2>pecto verify</h2>
<p>Check if code matches an existing spec file. Returns exit code 1 on drift.</p>
<pre><code>pecto verify &lt;spec-file&gt; [--path .]</code></pre>

<pre><code>pecto verify specs.yaml
pecto verify specs.json --path ./my-app</code></pre>

<p>Auto-detects YAML/JSON from file extension.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto diff</h2>
<p>Compare behavior specs between two git refs.</p>
<pre><code>pecto diff &lt;base-ref&gt; [head-ref] [--path .]</code></pre>

<pre><code>pecto diff main HEAD
pecto diff v1.0.0 v2.0.0
pecto diff HEAD~5</code></pre>

<p>Uses <code>git archive</code> to export each ref, then analyzes both and shows the diff.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto domains</h2>
<p>Show capabilities grouped by business domain.</p>
<pre><code>pecto domains [path]</code></pre>

<p>Clusters capabilities by naming convention (e.g. <code>user-controller</code> + <code>user-entity</code> + <code>user-service</code> &rarr; "user" domain) and dependency connections.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto graph</h2>
<p>Show the dependency graph between capabilities.</p>
<pre><code>pecto graph [path] [--format text|dot|json]</code></pre>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Format</th><th>Use case</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>text</code> (default)</td><td>Quick terminal inspection</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>dot</code></td><td>Graphviz: <code>pecto graph --format dot | dot -Tpng > graph.png</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>json</code></td><td>Integration with other tools</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<hr />

<h2>pecto impact</h2>
<p>Show which capabilities are affected when you change something.</p>
<pre><code>pecto impact &lt;name&gt; [--path .]</code></pre>

<pre><code>pecto impact Owner
# Shows: Owner Entity → OwnerRepository → ClinicService → OwnerRestController</code></pre>

<p>Uses reverse BFS on the dependency graph to trace all dependents.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto context</h2>
<p>Export a compact, LLM-optimized summary of the project.</p>
<pre><code>pecto context [path]</code></pre>

<p>Outputs a condensed text format designed to fit in ~4K tokens. Useful as context for ChatGPT, Claude, or other AI tools.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto report</h2>
<p>Generate a self-contained HTML report with interactive dependency graph.</p>
<pre><code>pecto report [path] [--output pecto-report.html]</code></pre>

<p>Opens in any browser. Includes D3.js force-directed graph, domain sidebar, and capability browser.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto serve</h2>
<p>Start a local web dashboard.</p>
<pre><code>pecto serve [path] [--port 4321]</code></pre>

<p>Serves an interactive dashboard at <code>http://localhost:4321</code> with dependency graph, domain clusters, and search. JSON API available at <code>/api/spec</code>.</p>

<hr />

<h2>pecto flow</h2>
<p>Trace the request flow for an endpoint as a Mermaid sequence diagram.</p>
<pre><code>pecto flow &lt;endpoint&gt; [path] [--format mermaid|json]</code></pre>

<p>Shows the complete call chain — from controller through services, database operations, events, and back. The default output is a Mermaid sequence diagram you can paste into GitHub, Notion, or any Mermaid renderer.</p>
<pre><code>pecto flow "POST /api/users"            # Mermaid diagram
pecto flow "GET /users" --format json   # JSON output</code></pre>

<hr />

<h2>pecto check</h2>
<p>Validate architecture fitness rules against the codebase.</p>
<pre><code>pecto check [path] [--rules config.yaml]</code></pre>

<p>Uses <code>.pecto/rules.yaml</code> if present, otherwise applies sensible defaults. Exit code 1 if any rule fails — CI-friendly.</p>

<p>Built-in rules:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>no-circular-dependencies</code> — no cycles in the dependency graph</li>
  <li><code>controllers-no-direct-db-access</code> — controllers must go through services</li>
  <li><code>all-endpoints-need-authentication</code> — every endpoint needs auth</li>
  <li><code>no-entity-without-validation</code> — endpoints with body need validation (disabled by default)</li>
  <li><code>max-service-dependencies: N</code> — limit service fan-out</li>
</ul>

<p>Example <code>.pecto/rules.yaml</code>:</p>
<pre><code>rules:
  no-circular-dependencies: true
  controllers-no-direct-db-access: true
  all-endpoints-need-authentication: true
  max-service-dependencies: 5</code></pre>

<hr />

<h2>pecto pr-diff</h2>
<p>Generate a GitHub-flavored Markdown behavior diff between two git refs.</p>
<pre><code>pecto pr-diff &lt;base-ref&gt; [head-ref] [--path dir]</code></pre>

<p>Shows new, modified, and removed endpoints, entities, dependencies, and flow changes. Designed for PR comments — use with the <code>pecto-pr</code> GitHub Action to auto-post on every pull request.</p>
<pre><code>pecto pr-diff main HEAD</code></pre>

